main event: A military pilot at position 64.N 172.00W at 2000FT reported four heavy black puffs of smoke over Champlinn area, which formed slowly and dissipated rapidly at regular intervals.
interesting points: The sighting occurred on 29 July 1949 over Champlinn area in Northeastern Siberia.
The puffs formed and dissipated at regular intervals of one to two minutes, with the weather described as 10/10ths coverage and unlimited visibility.
The report suggests that although the behavior was not exactly like known anti-aircraft bursts, the possibility exists that this phenomenon is anti-aircraft firing.
No physical evidence or photographs were collected as part of this report.
The report was approved and signed by Lt Colonel., USAF D. W. McKinney, Director of Intelligence.
